OL,3,CEnergy price cap predicted to rise in
OL,4,CJanuary, raising household bills by 1%
OL,6,FEnergy bills could be set to increase
OL,7,Fby 1% in the new year, as analysts
OL,8,Fhave forecasted a price cap rise in
OL,9,FJanuary.
OL,11,FEnergy consultancy Cornwall Insight
OL,12,Fsaid it expects Ofgem to announce a
OL,13,Fhike in the typical household's energy
OL,14,Fbill by #19, up to #1,736 from #1,717
OL,15,Fon January 1.
OL,17,FThe consultancy had previously
OL,18,Fpredicted a 1% fall, but said this was
OL,19,Fnow no longer the case. The predicted
OL,20,Fhike comes after energy prices rose by
OL,21,F10% in October.
