OL,3,CEnergy price cap predicted to rise in
OL,4,CJanuary, raising household bills by 1%
OL,6,FOfgem changes the price cap for
OL,7,Fhouseholds every three months, largely
OL,8,Fbased on the cost of energy on
OL,9,Fwholesale markets. The regulator will
OL,10,Fconfirm the level for the first
OL,11,Fquarter of next year on November 22.
OL,13,FThe energy price cap was introduced in
OL,14,FJanuary 2019 and sets a maximum price
OL,15,Fthat energy suppliers can charge
OL,16,Fconsumers in England, Scotland and
OL,17,FWales for each kilowatt hour of energy
OL,18,Fthey use.
